caption: Delicious. The food was perfect and so was try service.
Purple Onion is our go to place for a great burger! Their Onion Rings are awesome as well!

This little spot was definitely one for the books! It was a very classy, beautiful place! The staff was amazing and very friendly! We went for Valentine's day and it was perfect. $70 a plate. 3 course meal. The Moscow mule was delicious! The steak was cooked perfectly and the salmon was amazing! They had alive Pianist which set the ambiance perfectly. Highly recommend.
Amazing restaurant,  very romantic location.  Elegant and warm.  Definitely a place for a Date night or special event .
Great food. Filet cooked perfectly. Cozy atmosphere
Absolutely delicious food! Seasoned and cooked to perfection, great service.
Amazing service and food, as always!
As always the food was great as was the service and the atmosphere. been here many times and never had a bad meal always impressed and happy when I leave
Great place!
Wonderful place to eat. Great food and atmosphere 🤩  Our server James was absolutely wonderful and we enjoyed the whole experience.
Truffle mac & cheese was to die for. Best steak I've ever had! Love dining here.
Took my daughter here to celebrate her 50th birthday.  The food was great and the service was outstanding.  Will definitely go back soon.  I recommend the scallops.

Group outing for New Years at Cotton Row was simply amazing! The food was extremely good but keep in mind, you're paying for good food so don't shudder too much when you get your bill! I'd definitely do it again! The waiter was beyond accommodating, made some great recommendations and even informed us that gratuity was already added to the bill! Needless to say, he got more! If you're looking for an out of this world experience and top of the list standards in elegant dining in the downtown Huntsville area, be sure to put Cotton Row on your list!
Always excellent service,  atmosphere and food.  One of my favorites.
Decent

Twi thumbs up!!
Food was excellent. Service was amazing. Menu is somewhat limited. Overall, a great date-night experience.
Great good and service!⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

We made a reservation for 2 at Cotton Row to celebrate our first anniversary. When we made the reservation it asked if we were celebrating anything and we marked yes to anniversary. When we were seated the table was set for 4. Two of the place settings were picked up and the server did not mention our anniversary or ask if we were celebrating anything or even ask if we had been to the restaurant before (we hadn't). When we ordered drinks they took about 10-12 minutes to come out and when they did one of them was not what we ordered. We also had an appetizer and entree set onto our table that was not what we ordered that the server removed and brought to another table. We were only asked how our food was once and it was before we even had time to take a bite. The food was fantastic, but the service was not at all what we expected for a $$$$ ($166) meal to celebrate our first anniversary. Overall, we were pretty disappointed with our experience and will not recommend Cotton Row to our local friends.

Really, really special great food. The venison loin special and the scallop dinners were some of the best flavored meals I have ever eaten. I can only imagine that anything that you choose here will be special for you too. I will be back and most likely sooner than later. Nice job!
The halibut was delicious.
A go to spot for date night! Had a great meal and our server was delightful
Food was great
Excellent Food and outstanding service!

We worked hard in the field all day and it was around 7:30pm so my husband, being a farmer, saw the name of this place and said we need to try it. So we go in and notice that it is a nice dressy restaurant, but, we were hungry and tired so we went in anyways. Our service? It was HORRIBLE. And I’m not sure if it was because we were dressed in jeans and boots or that we are young “kids” (were 25) or that we weren’t drinking that night. Or maybe it was a little bit of all three. Our waitress? Well she let us sit for 30 minutes before she even asked what we wanted to drink. She would go to the table right next to us 3-4 times before she ever thought of coming to us. She never checked on us and NEVER refilled our glasses. I wanted to order desert but honestly I didn’t want to wait another 45 minutes for her to come over to us. What makes me so mad is the name of this place is cotton row, she probably has no idea what a cotton row is and obviously has no respect for a cotton farmer, the one who is the reason for the clothes on her back. She judged a book by its cover and let me tell you, my money is green just like everyone else’s and if I am going to spend that much money on a dinner I expect it to be worth it.
Very nice and elegant restaurant.  We are coming back soon!!!
Elegant atmosphere, tasty food!
Laid back elegant atmosphere.  The food is pricey but amazingly worth it.
Try the short ribs. Comes with grits. Great food. Great drinks

The sevice at Cotton Row is always fantastic.    In fact Cotton Row has the best service of any restaurant in the Huntsville area and is only challenged by a few. Menu and presentation follows in the same fashion.  Nice place hang out...

We opted for the dessert board which featured chocolate cake, the peanut butter and jelly in phyllo, and the creme brulee. The chocolate was good very rich and heavy, the peanut butter in jelly was different but tasty, but the creme brulee I could eat all day. The custard was smooth as silk.
Pork Chop was phenomenal, butternut stuffed baked apple was a delicious accompaniment.  My wife's short rib was perfect.
A well-deserved reputation and always a special occasion.  Even if it's just a finely crafted cocktail at the bar the atmosphere and service are a welcome respite from the grind.
The food was good...I can't complain. It was just unimaginative. Nothing crazy special. The workers and staff were the best part!!!
Great service! Our waiter was James. Did a phenomenal job!  Food is delicious!
Recently visited to celebrate my wife's birthday. The food was phenomenal and the service was exceptionally good. I could see myself visiting again.
Insanely good food...activates every part of the tongue.

Second time my wife and I have visited Cotton Row. First time was for our Wedding Anniversary. This time was just for a casual date night. As expected Cotton Row didn't disappoint! I had the 10oz Fillet and my wife had the seared scallops. Both dishes were absolutely delicious! The scallops are the best I've ever tasted in my life! Service was excellent just like the first time we went there and there was a musician playing nice songs outside. Now that we are living in Madison we will surely be visiting Cotton Row more often for the wonderful food and service. Highly recommended.
The husband and I have thoroughly enjoyed ourselves on two different occasions here. I highly recommend the Diver Sea Scallops! We will definitely be going back!
Food and drinks were a total 5 star. Service was fair, nothing special and the prices were OUTRAGEOUS. They don’t give you very much food either..
Great food! Super cool atmosphere with awesome service!
Amazing food, great service.
As always another excellent meal
Great service
The food was ok but not worth the price.  The service was good.
Treasures of the past. Great prices and deals.

Please note... Dinner & Cocktails: 5+++ stars Service: 2  I was excited to try Cotton Row for the first time. My husband made the reservations for August 27, 2020 and since someone reserved the entire first floor we were seated on the second floor in private dining which was a cozy and beautiful area.  I’ll start with the positives and that is our dinners were delicious and our cocktails were perfect! Upon arriving the man that greeted us and took us to our table was very friendly, made us feel welcome and wished me a Happy Birthday.  My husband ordered “Seared Cape Cod Sea Scallops” and I ordered “The Alaskan Halibut.” The scallops were seared to perfection & flavorful. The halibut was a very moist, delicious piece of fish served with perfectly cooked risotto. Again 5+++ stars to the chef & mixologist!  The downside was our service. Once we were seated our server Christian came up to the table handed us our menus and asked if we wanted drinks. There was not a friendly “Hi” or a casual conversation to start our dinner off. I mentioned my husband brought me there for my birthday and we were excited to try Cotton Row for the first time. He stared blankly at me with his mask on. He said he’d be back to take our drink orders.  The tone was set which also kept our ordering to a minimum. We were looking forward to a before dinner drink, appetizers, soup or salad and a dinner drink with our entrees. What we did instead was order one drink each and our entrees.  Our server did not recommend or suggest any appetizers, he did not let us know about any specialty entrees and pretty much was there to do the basics of his job which he did. To take a quote from J. Peterman from Seinfeld  “Job done.”  We have been trying more restaurants in our hometown (23+ years) of Madison County since COVID19 hit otherwise we usually spend special occasions such as birthdays and our anniversary in downtown Nashville dining at The Southern or The Farmhouse. The service was a 180 of what we are used to at a high end restaurant.  On a final note, the food can be the best of the best but if your servers that represent your chefs and their wonderfully prepared meals don’t care than it will prevent repeat business.
I love the Food and service we had in this Restaurant..
The beef short ribs are the best I've ever had.

Huntsville fine dining. A birthday celebration. Surf and turf sort of. Started off with the popular charcuterie tray. Cheese, meat, nuts and fruit. Special dollop od creole mustard seed caviar (waiter could give a better description). Wife ordered the diver scallops. Very well prepared, perfect sear. Nothing overpowered the scallops, as it should be. I ordered the filet mignon, medium rare. Broccolini crisp tender. The sauce was silky, great complement to the fillet. The potatoes gratin was amazing - creamy, cheesy, tender potatoes. We each ate half the plate and switched - surf/turf.  Dessert was an outstanding creme brulee. Fresh strawberries to cleanse the palate.
Was served a full plate of food poisoning, worst meal I’ve experienced in a long time.
Beautiful.  They really treated my brother like royalty for his birthday
This restaurant was absolutely worth it the braised duck was great.
Excellent food, great historical ambiance. Truly a breath of fresh air! Photo is of their Philo Peanut butter and Jelly.  I skeptical at first... but was delicious.
Sexy dining for two.

We each started with the crab cakes (best I've ever had!). Great flavor coupled with a delicious butter lettuce salad. This was followed by the filet mignon for my friend, and short ribs for me. Again - very nicely prepared, great flavor and melt in your mouth tenderness. For dessert - the heart shaped raspberry gelee for me, the choc/caramel torte for him. Thx
Bourgeoisie in all the wrong places. The food was sub-par, and very VERY overpriced. Get ready to lay down some serious cash for mediocre and  food.  A bit of an old money purple-hair hangout.
Romantic setting, soft music. Perfect for a date night.
Delicious through and through.   High end meals but so worth it!
One of my favorite places. Great atmosphere.
Fine dining. Great for special occasions! Staff very friendly and all masked.
Wonderful restaurant!!! Has 3 floors!!!!

We were here tonight for a private event. Everything we had from appetizers, to drinks, and dessert were absolutely on point. The pomegranate martini was fantastic! It did not disappoint! We will be back!

This is an innovative restaurant serving delicious dishes in a fine dining manner with American Southern sophisticated charm. Talented chef, amazing menu, friendly and attentive staff. Priced appropriately for the creative, unique fare.  I have returned here on every visit to Huntsville, AL and will again.

The overall experience was absolutely superb! The quality, presentation, and taste of the food was excellent. Portion sizes are a medium size, so get an appetizer while you wait if you want to leave full. The staff was very friendly, knowledgeable, and efficient. The atmosphere is quiet and stylish, great for an intimate evening. Keep in mind that it's very expensive; figure about $50-$60 per person before tax. Overall, a great special occasion restaurant!
They were very nice and loved old stuff they had but it's not a place I would choose

Great place for upscale dining. The duck plate was delicious and the staff showed up phenomenal service. Beer list was a little short but I presume most people drink wine over craft beer. Give them a try!
Great brunch.
Tremendous service and great food
Good dinner. Great staff
Fantastic food, fantastic service

Oh my, I didn’t think I could like Cotton Row anymore than I did. We’ve always been for dinner or lunch but finally got to try brunch and what a treat! Can’t wait to go back. First stop church, then Cotton Row for brunch. You can’t go wrong. The Twickenham breakfast was over the top. Can I get some right now? My favorite place to eat in Huntsville, Alabama. Great town and a serene place to dine. Great food, Wonderful service and top wine list.
Buitiful place, excellent service, tasty food
Cotton Row is great. The service at this restaurant is impressive. This restaurant would be good for any occasion.
Service was Great, Food was good.

There is no restaurant in Huntsville that is better than Cotton Row.  From the greeting at the front to the attitude of the wait staff, EVERYTHING says welcome and please enjoy.  The food is inventive, and always fantastic, and the experience is as good as any you will find - anywhere.  Go.  And enjoy...

Definitely one of the best-in-class establishments of Huntsville!  Their level of hospitality and service is nearly impeccable.  Tyler was our server/bartender at a hightop in the bar area and he was very observant and paid the perfect amount of attention to our table.  We enjoyed cocktails and small bites and the dessert was mouthwatering.  Highly recommend the PB&J dessert - I promise you won't regret it!
Attended a private party.  Food was fabulous,  especially the prime rib sliders.

Absolutely the best brunch in Huntsville. If you haven't been to Cotton Row in a while, then give it another try. Prices are very reasonable for the great service and excellent food. The overall experience was a delight, from the French Press coffee and fresh churos to the abundant entrees. This is my new favorite brunch spot.
Appetizers were amazing but my entree had a sauce that overpowered the taste of the lamb.

This is a nice restaurant, but it is getting sloppy. If I'm paying $200 to eat dinner, I expect better quality service and food. I felt like my waitress was rushed and rushing me. My food was subpar for this price range - for instance they didn't torch my creme brulee so it felt like i was eating plain custard. Not what I expect for this price range.

This one of two great upscale, quiet, white linen dining establishments in Huntsville.  It is also the most expensive, but the quality of food, service, and ambience justify the price point.  If you need a special occasion dining experience, this is the place to come.

One of two great fine dining establishments in downtown.  The price point here is quite high, but the quality of food, service, and ambience is deserving of the prices.  It's guaranteed winner of you need a special event dinner; they will not disappoint.

Went for the first time with a small party for a holiday dinner on a Monday night. The service was excellent, the place was full but stayed quiet, and the food was the best I've had in the area. Everything was cooked to perfection with terrific flavor pairings. The bartenders also went above and beyond.
Good food and nice atmosphere
Nice atmosphere, good food.
Wonderful food and service. Dining area is compact so I recommend reservations. Prices are on the heavy side but well worth it.
Loved the atmospher and the service was fast. I enjoyed my experience there and I will be returning for future dinners.
They are very polite to me and my aunt
Fabulous food..amazing service.. Just an incredible dining experience!!! We will be back!!

Delicious food and great service

Can only comment on Sunday brunch which was very good. Menu is small but a good mix and the food was very good. Full bar. It's small, only a dozen or so 4 seat tables so definitely make a reservation. All in all a very nice place to eat, would be happy to return to next time in the area.
Menu is awesome, something for everyone.

Before tonight, Hy's Steakhouse in Honolulu was our #1 all-around restaurant experience.  Cotton Row threatened to take the #1 spot tonight.  Started with the Fois Gras appetizer.  Filet mignon for me and scallops for her.  We told our server we were going to share the entrees, so the kitchen split the filet and scallops, the lobster mac and cheese, and the asparagus and gnocchi on two plates without us even having to ask.  Filet was ordered med rare..it was perfect all the way through.  Scallops were perfectly seared on one side to keep the tenderness through.  Lobster mac and cheese is delish.  Dessert was molten lava cake with ice cream.  The only thing that make Hy's better was the tableside chocolate fruit flambe.  My dry vodka martini was perfect.  I don't know how you could do it any better.  The staff at Cotton Row and the owner should be proud of their craft in such an unassuming location in a little city in North Alabama.  I couldn't stop talking about it while drinking IPA at a small brewery down the street.  Every penny was worth it.
Excellent
I got the Braised Black Angus Short Ribs and it may have been one 2/3 of one rib. Taste was on point, but not what I expected.
Absolutely amazing food and service!
Cotton Row is amazing. The service of this restaurant is fantastic. This restaurant is good for any type of occasion. I love this place.

Held a private dinner in their Cedar Pipe Room on Friday Oct 25.  Food and service (Manny) were great.  And Stephanie L. (who made our arrangements) went above and beyond securing flowers and balloons in place for our arrival at this 60th birthday gathering.  Well done.  Thanks.

I was really excited to visit this place because of all great reviews, but it unfortunately did not live up to the hype. I took my wife here for our anniversary dinner and was definitely let down.  The service was definitely the worst thing about this place. After being sat it took about 10 minutes to even be acknowledged by anyone and another 10 before coming over to take our drink orders. Our server never introduced herself, just asked if we knew what we wanted without providing any insight on the menu. Our  cocktails were served to us by another server before we got our waters. Service was like this throughout the entire dining experience, different people would drop off food but nobody came by to fill our waters or get us new drinks.  The food was better than an average chain restaurant, but for the price definitely not worth it. I will say my scallops were perfectly seared but lacked flavor and weren't garnished with any kind of fresh herbs. My wifes steak was cooked to temp and was easily the best thing either of us ordered. The cheese plate was okay, there was a lot of fruits and veggies and not a lot of meat and cheese. If this food came from an outback or something like that I would be impressed but its not fine dining quality for sure.  The decor here was super cool. It had a bunch of stuff from when it used to be a bank and they even kept the vault door. Dim lights, nice ambience made for a very intimate setting.  At the end of the night our bill was around 150 for 2 dinners, an app, and 3 drinks. I'm glad I got to check this place out, but in my opinion it's not worth the price. Especially for how bad the service was.
Nice decor for a restaurant, but the food is over priced for the quality. The service was very good, but a $20 for a hamburger and tea, was worth about $10. Will not be back.
We went to celebrate our Anniversary.  Food was fantastic. Perfectly cooked filet and scallops were best I've had. Would recommend for that special occasion!
Very nice
Service was perfect. Food was fantastic

Had a Sunday brunch here. Pricing was reasonable, menu is somewhat limited and skip desert. The lobster ravioli was good but only 4 ravioli, the fried green tomato benedict was good and a nice portion.  They have a nice wine menu and if they are out of the by the glass they will upgrade you.   We liked the relaxed meal but they don't attend to water or clearing of plates.   Skip the desert, I was looking forward to the lemon chiffon cake but I got a cold dense cake right out of the refrigerator.  Nothing light and airy about it.   The frosting was hard as a rock.  The ice cream with the chocolate crunch cake was delicious.  If you limit your choices you won't be disappointed.
Excellent dinner with a party of 5. Our server, Page, was outstanding as well was the food and all the other service!!!

It's very pretty and cozy inside however someone almost crashed into us and we hurt ourselves trying to get away from a crazy driver. We weren't offered anything even though we were coming into the restaurant. Then my meal was too spicy to eat and I wasn't offered a discount so paid a lot for a meal I didn't eat. I was celebrating a friend's birthday so didn't want to complain in front of her. But I'm very disappointed.
Great food and excellent service

Atmosphere the restaurant physically cultivated was excellent. The staff was polite, but a bit impertinent. One of my three companions ordered a tea, and it didn't arrive until an hour later. Probably just a mistake. The food was good, but a tad overpriced for the portions and quality. Not terrible, but definitely not --what I feel--  should be considered average for the standards to which that restaurant aspires.

And all their beef is PRIME (Connor's its a featured one per night).  Thus as such a fine estabishment, especially in a town with a bunch of top 10%ers, service and wine/food is FANTASTIC on a standard week night, but expect it to be overwhelmed on special event nights (holidays/weekends), as there are so few to choose from.
I can’t say enough good things about this restaurant ! The food was amazing so was the atmosphere upscale dining perfect for a special night out , I can’t wait to go back!
Food was great!

This is an intimate restaurant in a beautiful historic area with the beautiful name of  Twickenham. While they have valet parking available, do yourself a favor and park nearby so you can admire the historic buildings on your stroll. I had lobster ravioli for an appetizer and they were delightful. For a main I chose the deep sea scallops on greens and they were flawless! A crispy sear on the outside contained a perfectly cooked interior, not an easy task for a chef to accomplish. For dessert I chose a classic, creme brulee, and it didn't disappoint. The custard interior had a delicate kiss of vanilla and the carmelized sugar crust was perfect. Paired with an affogado, it was a nice ending to an wonderful meal. Reservations are definitely recommended.

Decided to take my wife here for out 20th anniversary. When we got our appetizer half way though it we found a hair under the batter of the green tomatoes. We got a simple sorry about that and you get a dessert. After that the service kind of went down hill we watch the what I’m guessing was the GM go to a every table and talk and visit but completely avoided us the food was awesome but I recommend dressing up because it seems they look down on people in jeans and tee shirts
I’m obsessed with everything that cotton row makes! This heirloom tomato salad with goat cheese is perfect!
Great Martini!
Too overpriced for food that is simplistic and underwhelming. They're basically banking on location rather than flavor
We came here for my husband's birthday and he fell in love with everything about Cotton Row. Service is professional but personal. Food is perfectly prepared.

First time eating here. Made reservations for my wife’s birthday. Was greeted at the door with happy birthday and welcome. Service was very punctual. Always checking to make sure we had everything we needed. I had the filet and lobster Mac and cheese, which I could eat over and over again. My wife had the flounder and she was also amazed. I will definitely be back. Great service. Great food.
Food and service was PHENOMENAL!!!

Best dining experience my mom and I have ever had. The staff was very friendly. Our service was exceptional. The menu was small, but in this restaurant a small menu means quality entrees. My mom had the ravioli dish, and I had the steak. We were beyond pleased with our visit to Cotton Row.
Delicious food and quaint atmosphere
Amazing dining experience. Our waiter was extremely attentive and knowledgeable about the menu and wine choices. Local favorite.
Amazing atmosphere and customer service. Perfect place for an evening drink.
Great atmosphere
Great food. Staff was friendly & accommodating.

Very nice setting. Optional valet parking, and excellent service. Lots of wine options and good libations. The food was delicious, but it is a little over priced. Free WiFi and there is a private room downstairs.
It's ok. Personally not worth the pricetag. Save your money and go to outback or Connors!
Elegant locale for outdoor dining, stellar service and delicious food. Live like an Italian and finish your lunch with espresso and cremé brulee.
Excellent food and service.
Food was okay, found a hair in my Flounder (waiter saw as i pulled it out of my mouth), didn't see a need in complaining. Nice atmosphere, had a pleseant experience.
Great atmosphere, attentive service, & delicious food
Special event location and always great service. Awesome meal.....
Very good, staff was great and knowledgeable, food was almost perfect
Great place for anniversary meal.
Very wide selection of foods. I ate fried green tomatoes and that was more than enough. Loved it!

I've only been to this place once. We don't usually eat at restaurants in this price range. However, I would return. The food was good, the service was good. No complaints. Huntsville has some pretty great places to eat. They have parking avaialable, or you can valet if you want. The menu has some great options.
Loved it. Excellent food and service.
Great food and service and an interesting wine list.
Good restaurant for a special occasion. Lunch menu was broad and food very well prepared. Nice patio and service was prompt.

I’m certainly a picky eater. In saying that, I not only ate items from here that I never thought I would, but I also enjoyed them. If the weather in right...try sitting outside. It’s actually in a part of Huntsville that has somewhat of a quasi view. Enjoy it and try something new you e never heard of. Local, fresh and excellent.

Attended an event upstairs and had a drink downstairs at the bar. Staff is extremely professional and helpful. Restaurant is beautiful and unique. The food was delicious! My only issue was that one person in our party was lactose intolerant, and the staff announced it with each dish served. She was gracious and said nothing, but I would have been embarrassed by the lack of discretion. However, it was all in all a fabulous experience, and we'll be back.
Great service, food, and ambiance.
Fantastic meal.  I will be back...probably many times.

Didn’t go to cotton row - because I know the food is overpriced and not that great.  However if you are parking downtown, DONT. Unless you want your car towed. They don’t label what’s reserved and what’s not. The only way we didn’t get our car towed was because the valet dude (who pulled up after we parked) informed us that we shouldn’t park our cars out front because the owner has a contract with the city. It would help if someone would put up a cone, or sleeve over the parking meter.... I don’t know something to say “hey this is for cotton row” The owner will have your car towed but fails to be a good business owner and state what’s reserved and what’s not. Pitiful.
The tuna burger was amazing
Delicious food!
Highly recommend
Food was good, not great for the price. Quality waiter and ambiance.
Wonderful place for a date, or special occasion. Very romantic, with a great staff that tend to every need.  We both had the Filet Mignon, and it was worth every penny!

We are in the upper room at Cotton Row and the setting was perfect.  Wait staff was very attentive and personable.  The food was the star of the night, grilled romaine salad with braised short ribs as the main course.  Dessert was chocolate cake with toffee I've cream and a special blend coffee that was the perfect ending to a great meal.
A bit too pretentious for its own good. The food is fair, but  lacking any sparks. The service was mediocre. Atmosphere is nice and would otherwise be prefect for a romantic night.
Outstanding food, ambiance and service.  On of my favorites in Huntsville.
Great atmosphere, and classic location
Great Experience
Atmosphere is perfection, Staff is strong, know their craft, and recommendations and pairings.  Chefs are on point with everything they make!

A friend of mine made reservations on a Thursday night for this restaurant. I had not dined here before but she had several times. We were promptly seated at our reservation time. The waiter was very friendly and helpful in suggesting choices from the menu. His advice was top notch, everything perfect from start to finish. This is definitely a special occasion, celebration, fine dining restaurant. I will be going back.
Great food...great bar tender

Really beautiful place. My girlfriend was very pleased. We ordered several appetizers. We had the the fries, fried oysters, butternut ravioli, and the cheese board. My family quite enjoyed the cheese board, fried oysters, and the butternut ravioli were delicious. The fries were basic and came with a homemade sauce. I ordered the grilled pacific salmon which was nice and seasoned well. We will definitely be back. Loved everything.
Cotton Row is my favorite. Chef Boyce & staff are top notch. Food is always spot on!

I have been to Cotton Row twice now. Both times the food has been great, but don't expect high end service here. This last visit was on a rainy Monday night, there couldn't have been more than ten customers in the place. We were there for a good meal while celebrating our 30th anniversary. My husband told them that we were celebrating when he made the reservation and once again when they called to confirm but not once did anybody acknowledge it once we were there. We were not looking or expecting any freebies but a simple acknowledgement or any attempt to make it a special night for us would of been nice. We won't be celebrating here anymore.
Can I give 6 stars?  Best Mac and cheese I’ve ever had.  Service amazing and the food was superb.
I could not have found a better meal.
The finest dining experience I've had! Absolutely delicious food and incredibly polite staff. Would recommend to anyone and would definitely go back!

I've only been to this place once. We don't usually eat at restaurants in this price range. However, I would return. The food was good, the service was good. No complaints. Huntsville has some pretty great places to eat. They have parking avaialable, or you can valet if you want. The menu has some great options.  We treat ourselves to this amazing place on our date nights. You cant go wrong with anything on the menus.

Was intrigued by the look of the restaurant on the outside. Found it to be quaint and attractively decorated on the inside. Service quick and accommodating especially for our 10 year old nephew. He enjoyed their cheeseburger and fries (He said the best!). While each of us enjoyed our entrees of the seafood chowder, ravioli, featured halibut, and the beef short ribs. All delicious and very well prepared. A delightful special occasion meal. Recommended.
Outstanding food and service... ask for a wine cellar tour, it's great!
Got a wagyu burger with truffle fries.  It wasn't anything special.  If I ever visit again which is unlikely, I'd go for steak.
I really love this place! The food is good and this is very nice and unique place to go!

Went to Cotton Row for lunch. We ordered the Short Rib Sandwich with fries and the NY Steak with truffle fries. The sandwich arrived towering with onion rings and the steak had a poached egg and an amazing sauce. The meats were both cooked to perfection. (I want more of that sauce) My only critique was my fries were plain. They tasted just like the other fries. Our server brought me more truffle oil and shredded parmesan cheese. ( This must have been inexpensive truffle oil because it did not have the kick of truffles that I expected) All in all, nice quiet atmosphere and cute dining area.

Third time to try this place. First time was with a fairly large group so gave them a pass. Second time not impressive. This time the service was ok.  Drinks were slow; water even slower. I live in Tokyo away from my wife and son and I was home for the holidays. I made reservations for New Years Eve and looked forward to having a nice dinner with my wife and son whom I miss very much.  We show up at the appropriate time and they tell us that our table isn't ready, so we had to wait for almost half an hour. There was no place to sit down so we just had to stand in a little corner by the hostess stand.  Finally after almost 30 minutes, the hostess took us to our table, which was upstairs. Strangely, she took us through the back through the kitchen itself and then walked us outside in the rain to a staircase to get to our table in a completely different section of the restaurant. I found this odd.  After we were seated, it took about 15 minutes for the server to bring us some water when there were only a few other guests sitting around us in the upstairs section of the restaurant. At this point I've been in the restaurant for almost an hour and all I've had given to me is one glass of water. I'm starting to get very irritated and my young son is starting to get antsy. This is not how I envisioned our New Years Eve meal to go down.  The server finally takes our order. I ordered the filet mignon (ordered to be cooked medium) and lobster tail a for me and my son and my wife got the chicken.  Again, we waited almost 35 minutes for our food to arrive, we saw our tray with our food sitting on a counter to be picked up. We watched as it sat there for about 15 minutes with no one bothering to deliver it to our table. We watched as many servers passed by it without looking.  At this point we've been in the restaurant for about an hour and fifteen minutes. When we got our food it was COMPLETELY cold and wasn't cooked like I asked. My wife's chicken was so dry that she could not eat it. It was like chewing sawdust.  I asked to speak to the manager.  I expressed my displeasure to the manager and she made the situation right and comped our meal.  The kitchen cooked our meals for the second time and got it right. From entering the restaurant to getting our correct meal took over two hours.  The couple that was sitting at the table next to us also had problems with their food and had to send it back as well. The gentleman that spoke to the manager was not pleased. He got cold food as well.  I'm glad that Cotton Row comped our meal, but I would have had no problem paying for it if it was done right the first time.

So I initially gave this review a 3-star, but was convinced by my boyfriend to give them a 4-star . . . Here is why.  This was my first visit to Huntsville, Alabama. I spent quite some time trying to contemplate on where to eat at. I usually like to go to chains for the reason of consistency in quality of food, taste of food, and service (which makes my overall experience). However, today I decided to go with trying something new.  The menu really caught my eye when browsing online. I must say the food was absolutely delicious! The presentation of the food was absolutely beautiful and everything was extremely tasty and delicious!  The service I received was excellent as well! My waiter checked on me constantly to make sure I was okay and even made suggestions. When he heard that I was visiting from out of town, he also made recommendations on their other three restaurants to try during my trip. He was extremely attentive and very nice.  My overall impression of the restaurant was very good. I like the presentation, ambience was very upscale and classy. They also have valet parking in the front as well as street parking. I'm assuming they validate and the waiter made a great effort to ask every single table if they needed to be validated, which was great because I always forget and have to walk back later to ask for validation after I leave.  On a scale of 1 to 10 I definitely give this restaurant a 10 as far as quality of food, and taste. My only complaint was the portion size. (That is the only reason why I initially gave it a 3, rather than 4 Star.) I didn't order an appetizer because I normally get full off the bread LOL I only had my entree I ordered the diver scallops. I also ordered my creme brulee dessert. With those two items I was just about almost full (that tells you how little I eat, but once again "just about" full.) The entree only came with 3 scallops that were about larger than half dollar size coin and served over zucchini pasta and mushrooms, which I felt was barely a side serving in itself. If I had not ordered the creme brulee dessert I definitely would have been still hungry and also I had two cocktail drinks to fill me up. Definitely for a grown man or someone with a bigger appetite I would say the portion size is very EXTREMELY small. My entree would be considered an appetizer in most restaurants. I spent about $70 plus tip for two drinks, and entree, and creme brulee.  I definitely would dine at this restaurant again for the ambiance and the service but if you are looking for a meal to fill you up, you will be spending a pretty penny. To be honest I could have ordered two of the diver scallops entrees and that would have been a full meal for me, and I don't eat a lot! For the price that you were paying, I felt like the value was not there, and after spending $70 to leave there not absolutely sure if I was full or not is not something I'm used to LOL nonetheless I had a wonderful experience and a great time. Like I said, I would definitely be back.

Overpriced, small portions and scallops that were rubbery and over cooked. Service was lousy as it took the waitress a good 10 minutes to even bring our check. Probably will not be returning. We ordered the Spanish Charred Octopus, and I realize octopus can be hard to cook and if done incorrectly it would be like eating an inner tube, well that was how this octopus was....an inner tube.  I had the seared diver scallops and the first one I bit into was also very chewy...a sign that the scallop had been cooked too long.  The other four scallops were fine.  Wife had the beef short ribs and they were fine and in fact tasted like a pot roast.  We had heard rave reviews about Cotton Row and having experienced it ourselves we are totally undecided about returning.  Hopefully Huntsville gets more upscale dining establishments as competition is a great thing to drive better dining experiences.
